Comments:	-- To start vmtoolsd:
		sudo /usr/local/etc/init.d/open-vm-tools-x
		The vmware-user daemon will be started when X starts.
		-- pcnet32:
		When using the "Flexible" adapter, the blacklist=pcnet32
		boot option must be used.
		-- DHCP:
		DHCP will be started by the startup script unless the nodhcp
		boot option is specified.
		-- GSO/TSO:
		If the ethtool extension is loaded, GSO and TSO will be enabled.
		-- Mouse integration:
		If /etc/X11/xorg.conf exists, the Driver line will be modified
		from
			Driver	"mouse"
		to
			Driver	"vmmouse"
		-- Resolution
		The screen resolution can be specified with the xvirt bootcode
		(xvirt=1024x768x24, for example) or in xorg.conf as shown:
		Section "Screen"
		  ...
		  SubSection "Display"
		    ...
		    Depth 24
		    Virtual 1024 768
		  EndSubsection
		EndSection
